ers. With contributions from authors in a variety of fields, Aspects of Urbanization in China creates a resonant and rich portrait of China's global ambitions, as well as their culture, architecture, and economy. While the volume deals with disparate aspects of urbanization, the articles included are unified by a deep concern for Chinese citizens.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aUrbanizationzChinazGuangzhou. 0aUrbanizationzChinazHong Kong. 0aUrbanizationzChinazShanghai. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aArkaraprasertkul, Non, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBracken, Gregory, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBracken, Gregory, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDreyer, Jacob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuo, Xiangmin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuang, Tsung-yi Michelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLiu, Changtao, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoya Pellitero, Ana M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScheen, Lena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSklair, Leslie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSolomon, Jonathan D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backfile 2000-2013z978311070067108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-201